{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn about how to set up your project with the new authentication flow changes."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"With the release of 0.26.0 comes a new migration flow for ATProtoKit developers. This change is fairly small, but this article will still cover what to expect in order to clear any confusion.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"Authentication Flow","type":"heading","anchor":"Authentication-Flow"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Previously, when you wanted to authenticate to an AT Protocol service, you used an initializer from "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"text":", which contained the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"handle"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"password","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" parameters. Then, you would use ATProtocolConfiguration.authenticate(authenticationFactorToken:) and passed the instance to the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtoKit","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let config = ATProtocolConfiguration(handle: example.bsky.social, password: hunter2)","","Task {","    do {","        \/\/ You can put it in here…","        try await config.authenticate()","","        let atProto = ATProtoKit(sessionConfiguration: config)","","        \/\/ Or here…","        try await config.authenticate()","    } catch {","        throw error","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"With version 0.26, this has been changed slightly:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let config = ATProtocolConfiguration()","","Task {","    do {","","        let atProto = ATProtoKit(sessionConfiguration: config)","","        \/\/ Enter the handle and password in here.","        try await config.authenticate(","            handle: example.bsky.social,","            password: hunter2","        )","    } catch {","        throw error","    }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Here are the changes being made:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"’s initializer no longer takes the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"handle"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"code":"password","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" parameters: now, ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)"},{"text":" is responsible.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This is the only external change. However, more has been made internally:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/UserSession"},{"type":"text","text":" is no longer stored inside of "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":": now, a new "},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" named "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/UserSessionRegistry","type":"reference"},{"text":" holds all instances of the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"struct"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UUID"},{"type":"text","text":" value has been added to the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"type":"text","text":". This value is linked to all objects that are related to the session. This is part of the new initializer for "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", named "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/init(pdsURL:keychainProtocol:configuration:canResolve:)"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" now closely follows "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SessionConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":". In fact, the following methods are no longer stored in the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"type":"text","text":", but have moved to default implementations of the "},{"code":"protocol","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)","type":"reference"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/getSession()","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/refreshSession()","type":"reference"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/deleteSession()","type":"reference"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A new ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"protocol"},{"text":", named ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":", will now manage the management of the password, access token, and refresh token. An ","type":"text"},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", named ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain"},{"type":"text","text":" is available for applications running on Apple’s platforms."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"anchor":"SessionConfiguration","text":"`SessionConfiguration`","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As mentioned previously, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SessionConfiguration"},{"text":" now has default configurations for each of the required methods. It is also ","type":"text"},{"code":"Sendable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and requires a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"text":" to conform to it. The default implementation assumes you’re using an App Password to authenticate by default, but you’re able to create new implementations for your own conforming ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Furthermore, the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)-272a8","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" method handles Two-Factor Authentication, but the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"protocol"},{"type":"text","text":" can also handle OAuth. This is thanks to a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AsyncStream"},{"type":"text","text":"-related properties, named "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/codeContinuation","isActive":true},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/codeStream","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Auto-managing-the-Keychain","text":"Auto-managing the Keychain","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"As mentioned earlier, a new ","type":"text"},{"code":"protocol","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"type":"text","text":" have been made: "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" respectively. This manages the keychain items for the password and refresh token, as well as storing the access token in-memory."}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The access token is being stored in-memory due to how frequently the token expires."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note","type":"aside","style":"note"},{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain"},{"type":"text","text":" conforms to "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and is the default object used for Apple platforms. It’s also the default object used when initializing with "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". However, you’re free to create your own implementation if it doesn’t suit your needs."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"At this time, Linux and Windows developers will need to implement their own "},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to achieve the same effect. However, default "},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"s for those platforms will be created at a later date.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note","type":"aside","style":"note"}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/atprotokit\/0210authflowchange"]}],"sections":[],"kind":"article","metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","title":"0.21 to 0.26 Authentication Flow Migration","modules":[{"name":"ATProtoKit"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/0210AuthFlowChange"},"references":{"doc://ATProtoKit/documentation/ATProtoKit/ATProtocolConfiguration/init(pdsURL:keychainProtocol:configuration:canResolve:)":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Initializes a new instance of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","title":"init(pdsURL:keychainProtocol:configuration:canResolve:)","url":"\/documentation\/atprotokit\/atprotocolconfiguration\/init(pdsurl:keychainprotocol:configuration:canresolve:)","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"init","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"kind":"genericParameter","text":"Keychain"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"text":"pdsURL","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"String"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"keychainProtocol"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Keychai